A MERN stack course covers the integration of four key technologies: MongoDB, Express.js, React, and Node.js. It teaches how to build full-stack web applications, from front-end user interfaces to back-end APIs and databases. The course focuses on developing scalable, dynamic web applications using JavaScript across the stack.

A React.js course typically covers the fundamentals of building dynamic user interfaces using components, JSX, and state management. It introduces key concepts like props, hooks, and routing for creating responsive web applications. Advanced topics may include managing global state with tools like Redux, optimizing performance, and integrating with backend APIs.

A machine learning (ML) learning path is a structured curriculum designed to guide learners through the various stages of mastering machine learning concepts and techniques. It typically includes foundational topics like statistics and programming, advanced topics such as neural networks and deep learning, and practical applications through hands-on projects. Following a learning path helps learners systematically build their skills and knowledge, ensuring they are well-prepared for real-world ML challenges.
